(File : AP) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Washington- US President Donald Trump is committed to providing military assistance to Egypt, White House spokesperson Sean Spicer said on Monday, after the new Republican leader spoke with counterpart Abdel Fattah al-Sisi.Trump "underscored the United States remain committed to the bilateral relationship which helped both countries overcome challenges in the region for decades," he said.Washington's annual $1.3bn in military aid was briefly suspended under Trump's predecessor Barack Obama in 2013, following the ouster of then president Mohamed Morsi, but was fully reinstated in 2015.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.